## Task

> Read @plans/review-report.md and plan the fixes for every finding in it. Write the fix plan to @plans/fix-review-findings.plan.md.

The review covers commits `8aa539a` and `3c9772b` on branch `uat-replay-0.12.1` -- Compodoc + Storybook integration setup for an Nx Angular library (`packages/ngx-smart-components`).

## Orientation Findings

1. Installed versions: `@storybook/addon-docs@10.3.5`, `@storybook/angular@10.3.5`, `@compodoc/compodoc@^1.2.1` (direct dep in package.json).

2. `setCompodocJson` IS exported from `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` at the installed version (verified via Read of `node_modules/@storybook/addon-docs/dist/angular/index.d.ts` + rg confirming `./angular` is a named export path in the package). The commit body's claim that it is not exported was incorrect -- it conflated `@storybook/angular` with `@storybook/addon-docs/angular`.

3. `tsconfig.lib.json` has `"types": []` (lib-distributable constraint). `tsconfig.doc.json` currently extends it, inheriting the restriction. The package-level `tsconfig.json` has no `types: []` and is the appropriate base for Compodoc AST parsing.

4. `main.ts` comment references a React-specific Storybook URL (stale, wrong framework).

5. `stories.ts:23` -- `.toBeTruthy()` on the result of `canvas.getByText(...)`. Since `getByText` throws when the element is not found, the assertion always passes and provides no value.

6. Docs-tab JSDoc rendering for signal inputs/outputs (the `sampleInput` and `sampleOutput` signals) is unverified -- requires running `nx run ngx-smart-components:storybook` and inspecting the Args table / Docs tab.

## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims

<pre_verified source="node_modules/@storybook/addon-docs/dist/angular/index.d.ts" claim_id="pv-1">
  <claim>`setCompodocJson` is exported from `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` in the installed @storybook/addon-docs@10.3.5. The correct import is `import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular'`.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
declare const setCompodocJson: (compodocJson: any) => void;

export { setCompodocJson };
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

## Relevant File Contents

```ts
// packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts
import type { Preview } from '@storybook/angular';
import docJson from './documentation.json';

(globalThis as any).__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;

const preview: Preview = {
  tags: ['autodocs'],
};

export default preview;
```

```json
// packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json
{
  "extends": "../tsconfig.lib.json",
  "include": ["../src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["../src/**/*.spec.ts", "../src/**/*.stories.ts"]
}
```

```ts
// packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/main.ts
import type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/angular';

const config: StorybookConfig = {
  stories: ['../**/*.@(mdx|stories.@(js|jsx|ts|tsx))'],
  addons: ['@storybook/addon-docs'],
  framework: {
    name: '@storybook/angular',
    options: {},
  },
};

export default config;

// To customize your webpack configuration you can use the webpackFinal field.
// Check https://storybook.js.org/docs/react/builders/webpack#extending-storybooks-webpack-config
// and https://nx.dev/recipes/storybook/custom-builder-configs
```

```ts
// packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/angular';
import { NgxSmartComponents } from './ngx-smart-components';
import { expect } from 'storybook/test';

const meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {
  component: NgxSmartComponents,
  title: 'NgxSmartComponents',
};
export default meta;

type Story = StoryObj<NgxSmartComponents>;

export const Primary: Story = {
  args: {
    sampleInput: 'Hello',
  },
};

export const Heading: Story = {
  args: {
    sampleInput: 'NgxSmartComponents works!',
  },
  play: async ({ canvas }) => {
    await expect(canvas.getByText(/NgxSmartComponents works!/gi)).toBeTruthy();
  },
};
```

## Source Material

The review report identified these findings (agent-generated; all verify-first markers preserved verbatim):

Finding 1 (Important): `preview.ts:4` bypasses public `setCompodocJson` API for undocumented `globalThis.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` key with no semver guarantee. Fix: `import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular'; setCompodocJson(docJson)`.

Finding 2 (Important): Docs-tab JSDoc render for sampleInput/sampleOutput unverified. pv-compodoc-1.2.1-signal-inputs (from review) confirms signal support is best-effort with known edge cases on type/default-value detection. Severity: Important (not Critical). `Run nx run ngx-smart-components:storybook and :build-storybook, screenshot Docs tab, confirm both JSDoc strings render before merge.`

Finding 3: `[verification unsuccessful: pv-compodoc-signal-jsdoc-rendering -- could not confirm whether Compodoc 1.2.1 extracts JSDoc from input()/output() function-call declarations into documentation.json properties consumed by Storybook Docs tab. Resolve empirically by running the storybook target and inspecting the Args table.]`

Finding 4 (Suggestion): `tsconfig.doc.json:1` extends `tsconfig.lib.json` inheriting `types: []` (lib-distributable constraint, restrictive for Compodoc AST parsing). Extend `../tsconfig.json` instead.

Finding 5 (Suggestion): `main.ts:14-16` stale React-docs URL in comment. Replace with `https://storybook.js.org/docs/get-started/frameworks/angular`.

Finding 6 (Suggestion): `stories.ts:23` `.toBeTruthy()` on DOM element always passes (`getByText` throws on miss). Drop assertion or use `.toBeInTheDocument()`.

## Question

Given that pv-1 verifies `setCompodocJson` IS exported from `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` at 10.3.5, and findings 2+3 require an empirical storybook run to close, what is the correct ordered sequence of steps to fix all six findings -- and should the empirical verification step (findings 2+3) come before or after the code fixes (findings 1, 4, 5, 6)?

